./.body:
How to initialize My Gitbook

Install Git

Windows 

Download


Mac

Check and install it
git --version





Install Nodejs

Download


Install GitBook
npm install gitbook -g


Install GitBook-Cli
(sudo) npm install gitbook-cli -g


Install sublime text

Download here

Launch it in command
ln -s /Applications/Sublime\ Text.app/Contents/SharedSupport/bin/subl /usr/local/bin/sublime


Package Control

Ctrl+Shift+P to search Install Package Control for the first use

search Package Control: Install Package to install

MarkdownPreview
go to Preferences -> Key Bindings to add shortcut keys:
{ "keys": ["ctrl+m"], "command": "markdown_preview", "args": {"target": "browser", "parser":"markdown"}},
{ "keys": ["ctrl+g"], "command": "markdown_preview", "args": {"target": "browser", "parser":"github"}}

go to Preferences -> Package Settings -> Markdown Preview -> Settings to enable autoreload:
{"enable_autoreload": true}


LiveReload
search LiveReload: Enable/disable plug-ins to select Simple Reload







Add a new SSH key

Specify your user info
git config --global user.name "your_username"
git config --global user.email "your_email"


Check if exsit
ls -al ~/.ssh


Create a new one
ssh-keygen -t rsa


Get SSH key

Windows
more id_rsa.pub


Mac
cat id_rsa.pub








Then add this to Github: settings/SSH and GPG keys

Tool/SSH.html.title: SSH
Tool/SSH.html.body:
SSH

SSH login without password(password free)
To set up a password-free login from service A to service B




In service A

ssh  mkdir -p .ssh
cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh  'cat >> .ssh/authorized_keys'





In service B

chmod 700 .ssh
chmod 640 .ssh/authorized_keys




Copy files
Add the followings to ~/.bash or ~/.zshrc




SCP utils

alias getf_from='f(){i="$1";j="$2";scp :${i} ${j};};f'
alias getd_from='f(){i="$1";j="$2";scp -r :${i} ${j};};f'
alias passf_to='f(){i="$1";j="$2";scp ${i} :${j};};f'
alias passd_to='f(){i="$1";j="$2";scp -r ${i} :${j};};f'




Keep SSH alive
Add the followings to ~/.bash or ~/.zshrc




keep SSH alive

alias ssh='ssh -o ServerAliveInterval=60'

RELP

All commands:help


Show the history:hi(story)


Search the history:h? 


Edit history for reference:e(dit)    //palce that line in recent history

:e(dit)      //place that variable in recent history


Then with a single up-arrow to edit/excute the code

Program/Scala/SparkScala.html.title: Spark
Program/Scala/SparkScala.html.body:
SparkScala

Installation
Install Spark 2.3


Setup shell environment
  Edit ~/.bash_profile or ~/.zshrc with



spark_shell_environment

export SPARK_HOME=.../spark-2.3.x-bin-hadoop2.x
export PATH=$PATH:$SPARK_HOME:$SPARK_HOME/bin
%SPARK_HOME%\bin #For Windows, add this to `envrionment variable`




Set log level
Edit conf/log4j.properties with
log4j.rootCategory=ERROR, console

Setup with the following levels: ALL, DEBUG, ERROR, FATAL, INFO, OFF, TRACE, TRACE_INT, WARN




setup_log_info_level

// set logger
import org.apache.log4j.{Level, Logger}
Logger.getLogger("org").setLevel(Level.ERROR)
Logger.getLogger("akka").setLevel(Level.ERROR)
Logger.info(s"")
